                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A 4e 1/63: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-05-01T17:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 1, 1924—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>84. With reference to the Department’s 80, April 24, 4 p.m., the Embassy at
                    London has reported<note n="36" xml:id="d506fn36">Telegram not printed.</note>
                    that the Foreign Office has telegraphed the British Minister at Peking that he
                    is to regard as definite instructions the views shared by the American and
                    British Governments as to the reply that should be returned to the Chinese
                    request for a preliminary conference, and to act with you in this
                    connection.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
